      <en>for</en>. Note that <strong>fad</strong> appears to be optional in certain contexts –</p>
    <xl>
      <li>3370</li>
      <li>3371</li>
    </xl>
    <p>Note also the comparable use of <strong>car</strong> –</p>
    <xl>
      <li>3369</li>
    </xl>
  </box>

  <box id="preposition-definite">
    <title><mark>fad</mark> as a preposition of temporal extent – definite uses</title>
    <p>When the temporal extent preposition <strong>fad</strong> governs a <em>definite</em> temporal interval noun, it corresponds to English <en>all ... (long)</en>, <en>the whole</en>,
        <en>throughout</en>.</p>
